Commentary: too short first up from around the wicket, and paddled fine. Short fine leg misfields and allows a brace
Commentary_short: Simi Singh to Hazratullah Zazai, 2 runs

Commentary: much better line, looped up on off stump and Zazai defends
Commentary_short: Simi Singh to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: fired in on the pads, and he went for a big slog over cow corner but misses it
Commentary_short: Simi Singh to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: flatter and quicker on off stump, turning away a tad, Zazai stays in his crease and wrists it to midwicket
Commentary_short: Simi Singh to Hazratullah Zazai, 1 run

Commentary: flatter on off stump, turning in a smidgeon, he stays in his crease and punches it down to long-on
Commentary_short: Simi Singh to Usman Ghani, 1 run

Commentary: looped up and a bit too full, Zazai slog-flicks it deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Simi Singh to Hazratullah Zazai, 1 run

Commentary: digs it in short first up, but on leg stump and Zazai helps it along the way to fine leg
back of a length on the stumps, he swivels to pull it off his hips to deep square leg
back of a length on leg stump again, seems to be a plan to Zazai to deny him room to free his arms. He tickles it around the corner
Commentary_short: Rankin to Hazratullah Zazai, 1 leg bye

Commentary: short outside off, and he slashes it to third man
bullet like Rankin errs in length, too full and on off stump, Zazai drills it straight back past the bowler, all along the ground for four
Commentary_short: Rankin to Hazratullah Zazai, FOUR runs

Commentary: and there's the Zazai we know. Fuller length again on the stumps and he clears his leg, frees his arms and sends this soaring over midwicket
Commentary_short: Rankin to Hazratullah Zazai, SIX runs

Commentary: good length on the fourth stump line and punched back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Chase to Usman Ghani, no run

Commentary: down the track, and over the top. Ghani converts this into a half-volley almost and swings it over midwicket. Didn't get it off the middle but got enough meat on it to reach the fence easily
Commentary_short: Chase to Usman Ghani, FOUR runs

Commentary: flicked off his toes that time and to the fine leg fence. Hint of movement away, but Ghani picks it up from off stump and twirls his wrists to send it fine
Commentary_short: Chase to Usman Ghani, FOUR runs

Commentary: tucks him up with a back of length ball outside off and he moves across to punch it to midwicket for a single
too short and Zazai makes good connection. Swivels and pulls it to the square leg boundary. Placed it to perfection, and got a boundary
Commentary_short: Chase to Hazratullah Zazai, FOUR runs

Commentary: good comeback by the bowler, bowls an away-swinger and Zazai wants to deposit it 20 rows back over the bowler's head, but he makes connection with air only, as the ball whistles past the outside edge
Commentary_short: Chase to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: flicked off his pads to square leg
thick outside edge flies over the slips for four. That was intentional. He didn't have any protection there, and angled it across Zazai, who slashed it up and over
Commentary_short: Little to Hazratullah Zazai, FOUR runs

Commentary: wallopped what power from Zazai. Stays in his crease and just sort of punch-flicks it past the bowler. That travelled fast
Commentary_short: Little to Hazratullah Zazai, FOUR runs

Commentary: way outside off stump and it's a wide. Zazai should get that run because he's rattled Little
and again! too wide again, trying for the wide yorker. Zazai was giving himself room but reaches out and carves this over cover. Off the middle of the bat again and flies to the fence
Commentary_short: Little to Hazratullah Zazai, FOUR runs

Commentary: stays just within the tramlines angling across Zazai and he lets it go. Not a wide
Commentary_short: Little to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: repeats the ball angling well across Zazai and ending up well wide of off stump, but just inside the tram lines. Two dots to finish the over
Commentary_short: Little to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: given lbw That was a close, close call in real-time and Rankin has a wicket. It's of Ghani, but at least Ireland have broken the partnership. Good length ball that came back in a tad, and Ghani was caught on the crease, trying to whip it away. Raps him on the knee roll right in front of the stumps. It looked out on first glance, and Rankin belted out and appeal long and hard until the finger went up.
Dismissal_text: Usman Ghani lbw b Rankin 13 (9b 2x4 0x6) SR: 144.44

Commentary: good length ball, coming into the right-hander again. Tucks it to mid-on
Commentary_short: Rankin to Najeeb Tarakai, no run

Commentary: stunning shot second ball he's facing, he didn't play the last match. Full ball and he lifts it over mid-on with a beautiful high elbow follow through
Commentary_short: Rankin to Najeeb Tarakai, FOUR runs

Commentary: dismissed It's like Afghanistan never lost a wicket. Length ball on the stumps and he's just whipped it over square leg
Commentary_short: Rankin to Najeeb Tarakai, SIX runs

Commentary: dropped by Peter Chase at short fine leg back of a length and coming into the batsman, who moved inside the line and tried to help it along the way. Chase dived to his right at short fine leg and got hands to it, but dropped it.

Rankin has got the big wicket, Stirling with a great catch Zazai gave himself room and tried to go over the top again, but only got a leading edge off a fullish ball that was moving away a tad. It swirls up high for miles, and Stirling runs back from mid-off and dives to hold on. He was never letting that go, he knew what an important wicket Zazai's is.
Dismissal_text: Hazratullah Zazai c Stirling b Rankin 31 (17b 5x4 1x6) SR: 182.35

Commentary: strays down leg and that will be wide
good length angling across him from over the wicket. He tries to swing it over midwicket, but misses
Commentary_short: Little to Asghar Afghan, no run

Commentary: quick ball, nipping back in, he's caught on the crease and struck on the pads. Going down leg so the appeal is only half-hearted
Commentary_short: Little to Asghar Afghan, 1 leg bye

Commentary: nicely stroked through cover. this might be the first shot of the innings that an Afghanistan batsman has just looked to stroke the ball rather than smash the cover off it. Gets the timing perfectly and sends it purring to the fence
Commentary_short: Little to Najeeb Tarakai, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length outside off, pushed to backward point
Commentary_short: Little to Najeeb Tarakai, no run

Commentary: good length, pitches outside off and comes back in, sneaks in past the inside edge off the batsman's uncertain prod
Commentary_short: Little to Najeeb Tarakai, no run

Commentary: too full and he comes on the front foot to punch it down the ground. Long-on runs around to field the ball
good length, stump to stump line, tucked to square leg
good ball, wide outside off, has him going for the expansive drive but misses the ball. It nipped back in a tad
Commentary_short: Thompson to Asghar Afghan, no run

Commentary: swing and a miss. Rushes down the track and wants to send him over the top, but it's another off-cutter and he misses completely
Commentary_short: Thompson to Asghar Afghan, no run

Commentary: full ball on off stump, pushed to cover
Commentary_short: Thompson to Asghar Afghan, no run

Commentary: back of a length, outside off, punched to mid-off. Asghar yet to get off the mark
Commentary_short: Thompson to Asghar Afghan, no run

Commentary: fuller ball on off, he waits for it and nudges it to point's right to get off the mark and keep strike
tossed up outside off, pushed to cover's left for a quick single
flatter on off, turning away, punched to cover
Commentary_short: Dockrell to Najeeb Tarakai, no run

Commentary: flat and on off stump again, steered to short third man
Commentary_short: Dockrell to Najeeb Tarakai, no run

Commentary: Balbirnie takes a good catch running in from long-on after bowling flat Dockrell gave this some air. Tarakai's eyes lit up and he went for the big hit down the ground, but got it off the toe-end. It swirled in the air, giving Balbirnie enough time to run in and complete the catch near mid-on.
Dismissal_text: Najeeb Tarakai c Balbirnie b Dockrell 17 (12b 2x4 1x6) SR: 141.66

Commentary: given some air and angled into the pads, defended back
Commentary_short: Dockrell to Asghar Afghan, no run

Commentary: tossed up again, and he comes forward to defend, but doesn't get to the pitch of the ball. It pops up in front of him, but falls safe
Commentary_short: Dockrell to Asghar Afghan, no run

Commentary: keeps it on a tight stump to stump line and Nabi can only punch it to the in-field on the off side
Commentary_short: Thompson to Mohammad Nabi, no run

Commentary: goes for the wide delivery to make him reach out, but misses his line and that will be a wide outside off stump
goes back to stump-to-stump, bringing it back in a smidgeon from a length. Pushed to cover
Commentary_short: Thompson to Mohammad Nabi, no run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, given some room and Nabi is quick to slash it down to third man. Chase runs around from fine to put in a diving stop
full outside off, but not as close to the stumps as his previous few balls and Nabi able to drive it fluently through cover
digs it in short and Asghar was prepared for it. Had moved across but was quick to transfer weight back and pull it powerfully through midwicket for a boundary
Commentary_short: Thompson to Asghar Afghan, FOUR runs

Commentary: short ball again, and Asghar nails it ever better that time. Swivels and pulls it, sending it over the man at deep square leg
Commentary_short: Thompson to Asghar Afghan, SIX runs

Commentary: stopped on the pitch, angled in and gripping and turning. He was too early into the shot but luckily for him, the ball didn't carry back to Dockrell
Commentary_short: Dockrell to Mohammad Nabi, no run

Commentary: given some air on off, pushed to cover
Commentary_short: Dockrell to Mohammad Nabi, no run

Commentary: too early into the shot again, but manages to punch it back past the bowler for a single. Dockrell almost got a hand to that, tumbling to his left
given some air and he takes a big stride to defend
Commentary_short: Dockrell to Asghar Afghan, no run

Commentary: flatter and quicker, fired in on the pads and he trickles it round the corner for  a single
floated up on leg stump and takes the pad to roll to square leg
Commentary_short: Dockrell to Mohammad Nabi, 1 leg bye

Commentary: too full and he punch-drives it over extra cover for a four
Commentary_short: Chase to Mohammad Nabi, FOUR runs

Commentary: pulled to square leg, but off the bottom half of the bat
too short again and Asghar is putting those away easily. Rocks back and pulls it, putting a lot of body into the shot and finds the gap between deep square leg and deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Chase to Asghar Afghan, FOUR runs

Commentary: better short ball, rose higher and was quicker, went past at head height.
Commentary_short: Chase to Asghar Afghan, no run

Commentary: too far outside off and that will be a wide. Got some shape away on it but lost his line completely
full toss on off, punched past the bowler but not with great timing
strays down leg and that will be another wide, second of the over
full on the pads, flicked off his toes to deep square leg
flattish outside off, driven firmly to cover
down the track and tries to slog-sweep it, but doesn't get hold of it. Sends it to the man at deep square leg on the bounce
nailed great use of the feet, comes down the track, gets to the pitch of the ball and swings it clean over long-on, high and handsome
Commentary_short: Dockrell to Mohammad Nabi, SIX runs

Commentary: flatter on the stumps, he stays back and punches it to long-on
flatter again and punched to wide long-on
fired in on the pads and turned to midwicket
Commentary_short: Dockrell to Mohammad Nabi, no run

Commentary: straight down long-off's throat Asghar wanted to lift this much higher but couldn't get underneath the ball enough. It was full outside off and he went low to lift it, but ended up hitting it straight to long-off
Dismissal_text: Asghar Afghan c Thompson b Getkate 20 (20b 2x4 1x6) SR: 100.00

Commentary: fuller on leg stump, tickled around the corner
Commentary_short: Getkate to Najibullah Zadran, 1 leg bye

Commentary: full ball outside off, steered to third man
length ball on leg stump, tries to flick it fine but it takes the pad to go to short fine leg
Commentary_short: Getkate to Najibullah Zadran, 1 leg bye

Commentary: fuller outside off, and he comes forward to drive it gently to long-off
loud shout for lbw, but that might have pitched outside leg stump. fooled by the pace and too early into the shot, he was trying to flick it but was caught on the crease
Commentary_short: Getkate to Najibullah Zadran, no run

Commentary: flatt on off stump, driven, but a good stop by mid-off, who dives to his right to deny the batsmen a run
Commentary_short: Dockrell to Mohammad Nabi, no run

Commentary: worked away to deep square leg
nails the reverse sweep Dockrell has been keeping it tight, this was outside the left-handers off stump but he went for the reverse sweep and beat the man at short third man
Commentary_short: Dockrell to Najibullah Zadran, FOUR runs

Commentary: take that too full and in the batsman's arc, he stays in his crease, clears his front leg and swings it high over deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Dockrell to Najibullah Zadran, SIX runs

Commentary: pushed back past the bowler for a single
quicker and flatter on the pads, he doesn't get hold of the pull-flick, and it trickles to short fine leg for a single
slower ball, and ends up beating the batsman's swipe, but just too wide outside off and it will be a wide
stunning timing inside out over extra cover he goes, barely a follow through and the ball sails over the fence
Commentary_short: Getkate to Mohammad Nabi, SIX runs

Commentary: full toss on leg stump, but beats his attempted swing that time. Gets an inside edge on to pad and rolls to short fine leg
good length on the stumps, he stays in his crease and pushes it to cover for a quick single
that's huge picked up the slower ball and dismissed it. Too full outside off and Nabi waits for it and swings it way over long-on and well into the stands
Commentary_short: Getkate to Mohammad Nabi, SIX runs

Commentary: good comeback, gets the wide yorker right and Nabi can only drop it to his feet while trying to carve it through the off side
Commentary_short: Getkate to Mohammad Nabi, no run

Commentary: you can't bowl a full toss twice in the over with fine leg up. He doesn't miss out this time and flicks it over the man inside the circle for a boundary
Commentary_short: Getkate to Mohammad Nabi, FOUR runs

Commentary: direct hit and he's gone Dockrell's the man at midwicket. Casual running from Najibullah, who pulled it to midwicket without timing and set off. Dockrell intercepted, turned and threw down the stumps at the bowler's end in one motion. He was well short.
short ball outside off, he tries to pull it but doesn't get hold of it. Gets it high on the bat and the ball hung in the air, but lands safely deep at square leg
short, given room outside off, Nabi steps away and slashes it over cover with great timing. Another boundary
Commentary_short: Rankin to Mohammad Nabi, FOUR runs

Commentary: fifty for Nabi stand and deliver for Nabi. Rankin dug it in short on the stumps again. Nabi steps away again, and flat-bats it over the bowler and into the sightscreen
Commentary_short: Rankin to Mohammad Nabi, SIX runs

Commentary: Nabi's unstoppable brilliant, brilliant batting. This time Rankin went full, he just cleared his front leg and picked up from the stumps, driving it over the extra cover fence.
Commentary_short: Rankin to Mohammad Nabi, SIX runs

Commentary: digs it in short again, Nabi leaves it alone that time. Not a wide
Commentary_short: Rankin to Mohammad Nabi, no run

Commentary: went for the paddle from outside off, went down low, but the ball gets a bit of a thick top edge and flies right over the keeper's head for four
fuller outside off, driven to the man on the extra cover boundary
monstrous They spent time changing the field, but every fielder is going to be a spectator if Nabi bats like this. Full ball and he gets underneath it, lifts it straight back over the bowler
Commentary_short: Little to Mohammad Nabi, SIX runs

Commentary: went for the yorker and almost nails it, but Nabi moves across and gets enough bat on it to send it fine, very fine and for another four
Commentary_short: Little to Mohammad Nabi, FOUR runs

Commentary: walloped again this was full outside off, too full. And Nabi has been sending those soaring again and again. He just repeats that, smashes it over long-off
Commentary_short: Little to Mohammad Nabi, SIX runs

Commentary: yorker goes wrong, ends up as a full toss on leg stump. Nabi whips it, and so powerfully that it screams across the turf and beats the man at deep midwicket. 25 runs off that over. Whew.
Commentary_short: Little to Mohammad Nabi, FOUR runs

Commentary: too full, driven powerfully but straight to long-off
back of the hand slower ball. Full on middle stump. And what does Nabi do? He stays still and drills it gun-barrel straight past the bowler. Into the straight fence
Commentary_short: Chase to Mohammad Nabi, FOUR runs

Commentary: caught at the edge of the deep midwicket fence that had air miles on it. Full ball from around the wicket, Nabi was aiming to lift it into the stands again and almost did it. Got more height on it than distance though and Balbirnie stayed rock steady, right inside the rope and caught the ball cleanly, ensuring he didn't step over. Nabi's fantastic innings ends
Dismissal_text: Mohammad Nabi c Balbirnie b Chase 81 (36b 6x4 7x6) SR: 225.00

Commentary: slower ball, from the back of the hand, and he gets an under-edge to the keeper. Way too early into the shot, beautifully executed slower ball
this time he bowls it quicker and on the leg stump, and the batsman is too late on the whip. The ball rolls to point off pad
another slower ball, Rashid pushes it to midwicket but because he hadn't timed it well, they end up stealing a second
keeps it too wide outside off and that will result in an extra. Wide ball
he misses the wide yorker again, and that will be another wide

pops out of Simi Singh's hands at deep midwicket He tried to time his jump right, but just couldn't get it, and doesn't manage to save the six in the end. Rankin pulled his line in a bit after those wides and Shafiq was waiting. Out came the slog-sweep, didn't nail it perfectly, but got enough on it in the end to just get away.

gets the wide yorker right that time, and has Shafiq throwing his bat at it. Gets it off the toe end and the ball only travels as far as long-off for an easy catch. They're checking for the no-ball, but Rankin looks to have just a millimetre behind so the wicket stands
Dismissal_text: Shafiqullah c Thompson b Rankin 12 (7b 1x4 1x6) SR: 171.42

Commentary: fuller on the stumps, flicked to deep square leg
slower ball, fuller length outside off. He goes for an expansive drive, but doesn't connect
Commentary_short: Rankin to Sharafuddin Ashraf, no run

Commentary: another slower ball, ends up as a full toss. He goes hard at it but without timing, sends it to long-off
good length outside off, pulled to deep midwicket off the bottom half of the bat
superb back of hand slower ball, dips on the batsman and completely beats him outside off. goes through to the keeper
Commentary_short: Chase to Rashid Khan, no run

Commentary: sliced up in the air but safe. Rashid wanted to clear cow corner, but he gets a leading edge with the bat twisting in his hand. Lands in no-man's land past mid-off
length ball on the stumps, driven to deep cover
slower ball again, and Rashid gets a thick outside edge that bounces to short third man. He's really nailing these back-of-hand slower balls
pacier ball that time, length ball on leg stump, and Rashid punches it to deep midwicket. Refuses the single though
great ball to finish, pitches outside leg and hits him on the pads. He appeals but it pitched outside. They run through for a leg bye
back of a length outside off, and Stirling shapes up to pull. Through his shot too early, clear lack of pace
Commentary_short: Ziaur Rahman to Stirling, no run

Commentary: full just outside off, and he crunches a cover drive through the infield! Presses forward into the shot, and times it exquisitely for four
Commentary_short: Ziaur Rahman to Stirling, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on leg stump, and clipped off his pads to the fielder at deep backward square. A jogging single for the duo
back of a length just outside off, and he rides the bounce to fend towards point
Commentary_short: Ziaur Rahman to O'Brien, no run

Commentary: length ball angling into his pads, and he check-pulls 'along the ground' to the leg-side fence! Whippage
Commentary_short: Ziaur Rahman to O'Brien, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on middle, and flicked off his toes very fine. Ball's in the air for a while, but short fine leg can't hold on to it. Ball flies over his outstretched hands, and that's 13 runs off the opening over
Commentary_short: Ziaur Rahman to O'Brien, FOUR runs

Commentary: beautiful shape first up. Full on middle from the left-handed pacer, and swaying away from the batsman. Tries to drive, but the ball goes past his outside edge to the keeper
Commentary_short: Sayed Shirzad to Stirling, no run

Commentary: length ball on leg stump, and he backs away before steering a checked shot to third man. Fielder near third man bends forward to intercept the ball, but the boots get stuck in the grass, and the ball runs away for four
Commentary_short: Sayed Shirzad to Stirling, FOUR runs

Commentary: back of a length on leg stump, with the pace taken off. Stirling's attempted pull comes off the bat's top half, and it's in the air for a while, but falls short of Rashid at midwicket
length ball on leg stump, and clipped off his hips to square leg for a quick single
Commentary_short: Sayed Shirzad to O'Brien, no run

Commentary: full on middle, slower ball again. Tapped off the front foot to cover, and they scamper across for one
length ball on leg stump, and angling across the right-hander. He can't connect with the straight drive, and the ball's through to the keeper
Commentary_short: Sayed Shirzad to Stirling, no run

Commentary: full on middle, but angling down leg. The keeper gets his body behind the ball to intercept
hammered! Length ball angling in, and he waits for the ball to come to him, before drilling a pulled shot into cow corner
Commentary_short: Ziaur Rahman to O'Brien, SIX runs

Commentary: length ball on middle, but going down leg again. O'Brien tries to flick it square, but can't get the contact
length ball on off again, and once again O'Brien settles onto the back foot, before check-pulling to the cow-corner boundary. In control, off the bat's sweet spot
Commentary_short: Ziaur Rahman to O'Brien, FOUR runs

Commentary: length ball just outside off, and the off-side tap comes off the bat's inside half. Rolls away to the leg side as they scamper across for the single
full on off, and he presses forward to defend with the bat's straight face. Played back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Ziaur Rahman to Stirling, no run

Commentary: full on off, and he clears his front leg to clear the infield. Plays a lofted straight drive, but he's toe-ended the shot, and the debutant earns his maiden wicket. Taken by Asghar at mid-on
Dismissal_text: PR Stirling c Asghar Afghan b Ziaur Rahman 10 (9b 2x4 0x6) SR: 111.11

Commentary: overpitched just outside off, and Balbo mistimes a drive to cover. Can't get off the marks
Commentary_short: Ziaur Rahman to Balbirnie, no run

Commentary: full on leg stump, and driven with the left-arm spinner's angle to long on
length ball, just outside off, and he rocks back, makes room, and then cuts this square past point for a boundary!
Commentary_short: Sharafuddin Ashraf to Balbirnie, FOUR runs

Commentary: length ball angling into him again, and this time he plays a late cut - steered very late - to pierce the gap between gully and short third man!
Commentary_short: Sharafuddin Ashraf to Balbirnie, FOUR runs

Commentary: length ball on off, and cut off the back foot to cover point
Commentary_short: Sharafuddin Ashraf to Balbirnie, no run

Commentary: length ball on off, but some extra bounce surprises the batsman. Fended off the back foot on this occasion
Commentary_short: Sharafuddin Ashraf to Balbirnie, no run

Commentary: length ball on off stump, and he covers his off stump, before defending from behind the crease
Commentary_short: Sharafuddin Ashraf to Balbirnie, no run

Commentary: sweet! Full on middle, and that's been lifted right over the bowler's head for a beautiful boundary. Holds his shot for the shutterbugs
Commentary_short: Sayed Shirzad to O'Brien, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on off, and the ball's going away from him. Tries to drive, but outside edge takes it down to third man instead
full on off, and the attempted cover drive is spliced towards the off side
Commentary_short: Sayed Shirzad to Balbirnie, no run

Commentary: length ball on leg stump, and pushed to cover point for a single. Slight hesitation for the single, and the throw from the fielder gets a direct hit! Balbirnie looks safe, and the TV umpire agrees
full on middle, and he chips a straight drive to mid-off for a single. Nearly takes the non-striker with him there!

length ball on middle, and he backs away to cut. Deceived by the lack of pace, and the under-edge takes the ball towards fine leg. Zia, the debutant, dives near the boundary, but he can't clear it cleanly. Another four from his misfield
Commentary_short: Sayed Shirzad to Balbirnie, FOUR runs

Commentary: length ball outside off, and turning away from the right-hander. He stays on the back foot, and lifts a back-foot punch over extra cover. Exquisite
Commentary_short: Sharafuddin Ashraf to O'Brien, SIX runs

Commentary: full on middle, and sliding down leg. O Brien can't connect with the flick
full on off, and nudged away to the fielder at square leg. Misfielded, but Ireland choose not to run
Commentary_short: Sharafuddin Ashraf to O'Brien, no run

Commentary: length ball on off, skidding inwards. Punched past short cover to wide mid off
sliced over the infield! Full on middle, and he opens the bat's face as he tries to drive square. Enough behind the shot to clear the infield, and the fielder at point gives it a chase
full on middle, and he takes a big stride forward to pull. Under-edges the ball, and that's enough for the ball to roll away to the fine-leg fence
Commentary_short: Sharafuddin Ashraf to Balbirnie, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on middle, and defended towards the leg side
Commentary_short: Sharafuddin Ashraf to Balbirnie, no run

Commentary: full on middle, and driven down the ground to long on for a walking single
full on middle, and driven down the ground to long on once again
length ball on leg, but skidding into the kepeer's gloves. They appeal for caught-behind, but not given. But in that distraction, the umpire does not call that a wide either. Smart from Afghanistan!
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to O'Brien, no run

Commentary: length ball wide outside off, and punched off the back foot to wide long off. The fielder runs around the boundary to intercept
full just outside leg stump, and clipped away to deep backward square. Rashid cleans up
full on off, and he presses forward to sweep. Played behind square, but finds short fine leg
full on middle, and driven away from his body past the bowler's left to long off
walloped! Full just outside off, and O Brien backs away before freeing his arms. Smacked over the bowler's head, and the ball lands beyond long off
Commentary_short: Sharafuddin Ashraf to O'Brien, SIX runs

Commentary: full on off, and defended back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Sharafuddin Ashraf to O'Brien, no run

Commentary: full on leg stump, and the attempted sweep is mistimed to fine leg
arm ball, short and wide outside off. He toe-ends a cut-shot to cover
length ball just outside off, but the delivery stays low. Bends his knees to cut, but the shot finds point
Commentary_short: Sharafuddin Ashraf to Balbirnie, no run

Commentary: length ball, wide outside off, and cut off the back foot to point
full on middle, and tapped with soft hands to midwicket. Could've been a tight run had midwicket collected the ball in one motion
length ball on middle, and he backs away to punch. Ball holds it's line, so KoB needs to adjust. Bunted down the ground to long on for one
full on middle, and steered away to short third man. Nice, early call for a single
full on leg stump, and punched down the ground to long on. Walks across to the other end, but doesn't celebrate despite his fifty! Means one thing: O'Brien wants to finish this game off
length ball, just outside off, and he makes room before cutting past backward point for another boundary to end the over
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Balbirnie, FOUR runs

Commentary: drags this short, and the set O'Brien has no trouble in putting this away. Drags a pull from outside off stump, and deposits this to the leg-side boundary
Commentary_short: Ziaur Rahman to O'Brien, FOUR runs

Commentary: length ball angling in, and flicked away to the fine-leg region
full on leg, and driven down the ground to long on for a single
back of a length, really wide outside off, and slapped down to wide mid-off for one
length ball on middle, and glanced away towards short third man for a single. Keeper runs to his right to intercept
length ball angling into his body, and nudged off his hips to deep backward square. Hundred for Ireland
full outside off, and slapped away from his body to point for one
full just outside off, and the slider is tapped away to Asghar at gully. They scamper across for one
length ball on middle, and spinning into his pads. Flicked to deep midwicket for a single
full just outside off stump, and driven away from his body to third man
full on middle, and driven down the ground to wide mid-on. They scamper across for one
length ball on middle, and flicked away to midwicket for a walking single
overpitched on middle, and the attempted straight drive nearly goes to Nabi! Falls just short
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Balbirnie, no run

Commentary: lifted inside out over cover! Full on middle, but he backs away exposing all three stumps. Drives over the infield thereafter, and Rashid - at wide long off - can't cut it off
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Balbirnie, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on middle, and nudged off his pads to square leg for a quick one
length ball on off, and bunted down the ground to long off for a walking single
full on off, and swept hard to deep midwicket
length ball on middle, and punched down the ground to long off for another single

dropped at deep backward square! Shirzad makes a mess of it. Quicker ball outside leg stump, and the attempted slog-sweep found the fielder. Ball pops out of his hand and that gives the set KoB another life
full on middle, and driven down the ground to long on for a single
full on middle, and he muscles a sweep to deep backward square once again. This time... along the ground
back of a length on middle, and the ball hits the batsman's body. Can't pull this away because the bowler followed the batsman
Commentary_short: Sharafuddin Ashraf to O'Brien, no run

Commentary: full on off, and muscled past the bowler's left to long off
length ball, just outside off, and chopped on to short third man for one
length ball skidding inwards, and his attempted cut is almost chopped onto his stumps. Ball goes towards the keeper's right
length ball angling in, and the attempted pull is inside-edged onto his body. Ball dribbles away to the leg side as Balbirnie tells O'Brien to take the single

crunched inside out over cover! Balbirnie's making some moves now. Backs away before the bowler delivers the ball, the delivery lands on middle, and Balbirnie absolutely hammers a lofted drive to the extra-cover boundary
Commentary_short: Ziaur Rahman to Balbirnie, FOUR runs

Commentary: slower ball does the trick! Big wicket. Full just outside off, but the slower ball deceives the batsman. He presses forward to defend, but he's playing outside the ball's line. Big gap between bat and body, and the ball sneaks through
Dismissal_text: A Balbirnie  b Ziaur Rahman 47 (33b 7x4 0x6) SR: 142.42

Commentary: full just outside off, and he backs away before cutting to point. Stopped by the fielder

direct hit! But it's Thompson whose gone, and not o'Brien. The batsman had slapped a shot to point and gone for the single, but the fielder at point stops the ball, then aims at the stumps, and Zadran's throw finds the stumps at the batsman's end
Dismissal_text: SR Thompson run out (Najibullah Zadran) 1 (1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 100.00

Commentary: full on middle, and the leg-side whip nearly goes all the way to the fielder at long on. Bounces just before him as O'Brien moves on to 69
length ball on leg stump, and worked off his hips to deep midwicket for a walking single
length ball on middle, and the attempted cut takes an inside edge. Rolls down to Rashid at midwicket
length ball, slower ball, and O'Brien muscles his pull to deep midwicket. But fielder there. Smart bowling from Shirzad
full on middle, and he picks this ball early! Gets under the delivery and paddles a six over fine leg! Innovative
Commentary_short: Sayed Shirzad to Dockrell, SIX runs

Commentary: chipped over cover! Full outside off, and Dockrell's forced to reach at it. Toe-ends a drive over Nabi, but falls just beyond him
length ball outside off, and the legbreak is muscled down to long off for one

full on off, and he drags a slog sweep to the leg side. Usman's running across the boundary there, but his one-handed parry can't pull the ball back. Another disappointing fielder effort from Afghanistan's outfielders
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Dockrell, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on off, and the wrong-un is pulled along the ground to deep midwicket
length ball outside leg stump, and spinning further down the leg side. O Brien misses the flick, but so does the keeper. Chase for fine leg running across the boundary
full on middle, and he hammers a flat-batted shot to long on for one
full on leg stump, and he drags a pull to cow corner for a walking single

finger goes up! Full and wide outside off, and O'Brien makes room to drive. Ball turns away from him, and that's taken a slight toe-end off his bat. Keeper holds on, and the umpire raises his finger. O'Brien gave his wicket away by looking at the keeper after missing shot. Umpires often catch on to those signs. Huge, huge wicket
Dismissal_text: KJ O'Brien c †Shafiqullah b Rashid Khan 74 (47b 5x4 3x6) SR: 157.44

Commentary: full and wide outside off, and the attempted straight drive comes off the bat's inside-half. It rolls away to long on
full just outside off, and he drills a straight drive to long off
nearly a yorker on off stump. He drigs a straight drive to long on for a single. They want two, but Zadran's effort in the deep ensures it's just a single
low full toss on middle. Driven straight back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Getkate, no run

Commentary: full ball on middle, and he bunts this down to long on once again. Just the one run
full just outside off stump, and he muscles a drive to wide long-on again. Nabi finishes with 0 for 28

what a screamer! Nabi, you beauty! Full just outside off, and the batsman slog sweeps towards wide long-on. Has six written all over it, but Nabi jumps near the ropes, takes the catch, throws it in the air as he's falling over the boundary, then composes himself and eventually completes a 360-degree take.
Dismissal_text: GH Dockrell c Mohammad Nabi b Rashid Khan 18 (10b 1x4 1x6) SR: 180.00

Commentary: length ball on off, and the wrong'un comes into Getkate. The batsman's come half-way down the wicket, and the ball has sneaked under his bat. Keeper does extremely well staying low and collecting the ball, and then whips the bails off to hand Rashid another scalp. Shafiq excellent behind the stumps too. Hat-trick!
Dismissal_text: SC Getkate st †Shafiqullah b Rashid Khan 2 (4b 0x4 0x6) SR: 50.00

Commentary: double hat-trick! Length ball on off, and the googly skids inwards. Misses the leg-side flick, and the ball hits his knee roll. Rashid's appealing for lbw, and the umpire raises his finger. As easy as A-B-C
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Simi Singh, OUT
Dismissal_text: Simi Singh lbw b Rashid Khan 0 (1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00

Commentary: full on middle, and he walks across the stumps to try and sweep. Misses the ball completely, and the delivery just sneaks past leg stump as well. Could've had five in five, but just slightly inaccurate
length ball just outside off, and defended towards cover
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Poynter, no run

Commentary: full on middle, and pushed down to long on for a single. Direct hit from mid-on means that Ireland can pinch another single
length ball on off, and worked off his pads to square leg for one
full just outside off, and driven away from his body to third man
length ball, outside leg stump, and nudged away to fine leg for a run
full on middle, and flicked over the square-leg umpire for four
Commentary_short: Sayed Shirzad to Poynter, FOUR runs

Commentary: length ball, just outside off, and muscled to cover for a single
full on off, and he drills this straight. Usman Ghani, at long on, has no chance either
Commentary_short: Sayed Shirzad to Little, FOUR runs

Commentary: full just outside off, and he drags an attempted slog to long on. Ireland need 36 off the final over
length ball, just outside off, and he can't connect with the googly. Through to the keeper
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Little, no run

Commentary: off stump gone! Another five-wicket haul. Full outside off stump, and spinning into Little. He goes for a wild sweep, and the the wrong'un goes past his pads and clips the outside of off stump
Dismissal_text: JB Little  b Rashid Khan 6 (5b 1x4 0x6) SR: 120.00

Commentary: length ball on middle, and whipped away to square leg for a single
full on middle, and the ball stays low. Can't flick it square
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Poynter, no run

Commentary: full just outside off stump, and pushed away from his body to point
worked away to the leg side, and Afghanistan win by 32 runs!
